## What mbuzz is (canonical positioning)

mbuzz is a multi-touch attribution platform for technical marketers who have stopped trusting their dashboard. Every attribution tool ships with a model baked in — last-click, data-driven, proprietary — and reports its number as if it came from physics. It does not. The same data, run through different models, produces completely different answers.

mbuzz is the only attribution tool in the category that runs eight models side-by-side (first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay, position-based, Markov, Shapley, data-driven) and lets you write your own in a SQL-like Attribution DSL. All of it runs server-side for 30–40% more touchpoint capture than client-side trackers miss to ad blockers and iOS privacy. Open-source SDKs for Ruby, Node, Python, and PHP mean the whole thing is code you can inspect and own.

Built for startups and mid-market companies spending $20K–$1M per month on paid media who want to audit the math themselves — not pay $5K per month for someone else's opinion.

