## Tier 1 features (the wedge — what only mbuzz does)

1. **Multi-model attribution** — eight models on the same data simultaneously. Buyers see the spread between models, not a single hidden answer. If Markov says Google is 40% of credit and last-touch says 15%, the real answer lives in the fight between models.
2. **Attribution DSL** — a SQL-like language for editing or writing custom attribution models. Nested time windows, custom decay curves, segment-specific logic. Free 0 / Starter 3 / Growth 5 / Pro 10 custom slots.
3. **Lossless tracking** — server-side capture of 30–40% more touchpoints than client-side trackers miss to ad blockers and iOS privacy. The math can only be honest if the data is complete.
4. **Data ownership** — full export on every plan via CSV, API, and MCP. No premium-tier gate. Customers can pipe data into BigQuery, Snowflake, or any warehouse.

