## Methodology — what mbuzz does NOT claim

mbuzz is a better multi-touch attribution platform with model transparency. mbuzz does NOT solve incrementality. Click attribution — what mbuzz does — has been shown to overstate causal impact by 2–10× compared to geo-incrementality experiments (Chivukula et al., IEEE Access, March 2026, Dropbox engineering team). mbuzz makes the model and the data visible; it does not run causal experiments.

If a customer needs causal measurement they should use Haus, Measured, Recast, or run their own geo-holdout tests at the budget those require. mbuzz is the layer underneath: more accurate touchpoint data, multiple models for honest range estimates, and the code-level transparency that makes the math auditable.

