## Why now (market trend)

Three overlapping signals make 2026 the urgent year to pick a side on attribution:

1. **GA4 removed its attribution models in 2023.** Every marketer who relied on first-click, last-click, or rule-based attribution inside GA4 now has nothing. Forced migration window.
2. **Platform self-reporting is now publicly admitted to inflate.** The Dropbox IEEE paper (March 2026) showed click attribution overstates 2–10× vs causal. Meta restructured click attribution late March 2026. Buyers are ready to hear the wedge.
3. **AI agents are becoming marketing decision-makers.** HockeyStack's Revenue Agents, SegmentStream's AI, Haus's MIA. Every vendor is racing to put AI on top of attribution data. Bad data at agent speed burns money fast. The agents need accurate, machine-readable, model-inspectable attribution underneath them. mbuzz's DSL and API shape are pre-built for this.

